                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d305">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 War Credits/588: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece (<persName type="from">Morris</persName>)
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-28T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 28, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 28—8:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>140. My 135, November 12 [<hi rend="italic">22</hi>], 7 p.m. International
                    Financial Commission presented November 26 note to Minister of Finance calling
                    for transfer of 30 percent interest on loans under its control. The American
                    1929, 4 percent loan was included in the list. I will telegraph Greek answer to
                    the Commission which is expected to be received tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
